notes.text: Participants are required to fast before Visits 1-12. See Section 5.3.1. If a participant arrives not fasted, schedule the laboratory draw for another date.
Visit 1 procedures may be conducted over more than 1 day if all activities are completed within the allowable visit tolerance.
The ICF must be signed before any protocol-specific tests or procedures are performed. See Appendix 10.1.3 for additional details.
Inclusion and exclusion criteria should be confirmed prior to drug assignment and administration of first dose of study intervention.
High risk for cardiovascular events will be defined as CAD, stroke, or peripheral artery disease, or ASCVD risk equivalents (familial hypercholesterolemia or type 2 diabetes)
Includes year of birth, sex, ethnicity (where permissible), and race.
All conditions ongoing and relevant past surgical and medical history should be collected.
Prespecified medical history includes history of cardiovascular events.
Relevant prior therapies include, but are not limited to, lipid-lowering medications.
Additional data will be collected for medications of interest.
Any events that occur after signing the informed consent are considered AEs as defined (Appendix 10.3). Additional data are collected for certain AEs.
Participant should remove shoes.
Includes pulse rate and blood pressure measured after participant has been sitting at least 5 minutes and before ECG tracing and collection of blood samples for laboratory testing.
The physical examination is performed (excludes pelvic, rectal, and breast examinations unless clinically indicated).
Symptom-directed physical assessment will be conducted at the discretion of the PI or qualified personnel, per local regulations, as indicated based on participant status and standard of care.

Collect single, local ECG prior to collection of blood samples for laboratory testing, including PK samples. Participants should be supine for approximately 5 to 10 minutes before ECG collections and remain supine but awake during the ECG collection. ECGs may be repeated at the PI's discretion at any visit. See Section 8.2.1.
Females only.
Optional; performed as needed to confirm postmenopausal status. See Appendix 10.4.
Calculated using CKD-EPI method.
Visit 2: Collect 2 samples. 0.5 hours postdose, 4-9 hours postdose (minimum 2 hours). Visit 7: Collect 1 sample. 24-36 hours postdose, will require participant to return 1 day after Visit 7.
Visit 2 and 7 will be collected predose.
Collect a time-matched PK sample for all scheduled and unscheduled immunogenicity samples. Visit 7 will be collected predose.
Sample can be obtained at or after the specified visit. See Appendix 10.5.
On dosing days, collect samples before dosing
Unscheduled visits are not required to be registered in IWRS.
If HCV antibody test is positive, it must be followed by an HCV RNA test. See Section 8.2.5.
If HBsAg is negative and HBcAb is positive, further testing with HBV DNA is required. If the screening HBV DNA is negative, the participant is not excluded. See Section 8.2.4.

conditions.name: Lp(a) Eligibility Criteria
conditions.text: Participants with Lp(a) <175 nmol/L at Visit 1 will not be eligible for enrollment, despite their values in prescreening

conditions.name: High Risk for Cardiovascular Events
conditions.description: Definition of high cardiovascular risk status
conditions.text: High risk for cardiovascular events will be defined as CAD, stroke, or peripheral artery disease, or ASCVD risk equivalents (familial hypercholesterolemia or type 2 diabetes)

conditions.name: Fasting Requirement
conditions.text: Participants are required to fast before Visits 1-12. If a participant arrives not fasted, schedule the laboratory draw for another date

conditions.name: HCV Positive Follow-up
conditions.description: Additional testing required if HCV antibody positive
conditions.text: If HCV antibody test is positive, it must be followed by an HCV RNA test

conditions.name: HBV Screening Follow-up
conditions.description: Additional testing for hepatitis B status
conditions.text: If HBsAg is negative and HBcAb is positive, further testing with HBV DNA is required. If the screening HBV DNA is negative, the participant is not excluded

conditions.name: FSH Testing Condition
conditions.description: Optional FSH testing for postmenopausal confirmation
conditions.text: Optional; performed as needed to confirm postmenopausal status

transitionRules.name: Prescreening to Screening Transition
transitionRules.text: If the participant has not had Lp(a) measured before or is unknown, the prescreening visit should be completed. Central laboratory testing for Lp(a) is still required as part of the screening procedures conducted at Visit 1

transitionRules.name: Screening to Treatment Transition
transitionRules.text: Inclusion and exclusion criteria should be confirmed prior to drug assignment and administration of first dose of study intervention. All procedures (screening and baseline) need to be completed prior to the first dose of study intervention

transitionRules.name: Prescreening Repeat Rule
transitionRules.text: The optional prescreening visit can be repeated 1 time (no more) per participant if the investigator believes the participant would meet criteria at a later time, with a minimum of 4 weeks between visits. Repeated sampling in the prescreening visit will not require re-consenting or assignment of a new participant identification number

transitionRules.name: Early Discontinuation from Study Intervention
transitionRules.text: For an early discontinuation (ED) from the study intervention that occurs before the last visit in treatment period, see the activities listed for ED in this table

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Early Discontinuation
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Early discontinuation from study intervention before the last visit in treatment period triggers ED visit procedures

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lp(a) Screening Failure
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participants with Lp(a) <175 nmol/L at Visit 1 will not be eligible for enrollment

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Protocol J3L-MC-EZEB approved on 19 Jul 2022 GMT

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Added optional prescreening period (Period I) with Visit 601 for Lp(a) assessment
Clarified that Visit 1 procedures may be conducted over more than 1 day if all activities are completed within the allowable visit tolerance
Added provision for prescreening visit to be repeated once with minimum 4 weeks between visits
Specified that prescreening visit timing deviation from 21 days will not be considered a protocol deviation

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: To provide a simple way for sites to determine whether participants meet Lp(a) criteria before full screening activities are initiated
To allow flexibility in prescreening location including study site, mobile healthcare, or alternate laboratory
To accommodate participants who may meet Lp(a) criteria at a later time by allowing one repeat of prescreening

studyChanges.afterText: Period I - Optional Prescreening: The study includes an optional prescreening visit (Visit 601) as a simple way for sites to determine whether participants meet Lp(a) criteria, as assessed by a central laboratory assessment, before the full screening activities are initiated at Visit 1.
studyChanges.summary: Added new optional prescreening period (Period I) with Visit 601 for Lp(a) assessment

studyChanges.afterText: The prescreening visit can be conducted at the study site, or remotely, for example, at a mobile healthcare or alternate laboratory.
studyChanges.summary: Added flexibility for prescreening visit location

studyChanges.afterText: The optional prescreening visit can be repeated 1 time (no more) per participant if the investigator believes the participant would meet criteria at a later time, with a minimum of 4 weeks between visits.
studyChanges.summary: Added provision for one repeat of prescreening visit with 4-week minimum interval

studyChanges.afterText: Repeated sampling in the prescreening visit will not require re-consenting or assignment of a new participant identification number.
studyChanges.summary: Clarified that repeat prescreening does not require new consent or participant ID

studyChanges.afterText: A prescreening visit occurring longer or shorter than 21 days (3 weeks) from screening will not be considered a protocol deviation.
studyChanges.summary: Clarified that prescreening timing deviation is not a protocol deviation

studyChanges.beforeText: Visit 1 procedures may be conducted over more than 1 day as long as all activities are completed prior to Visit 2.
studyChanges.afterText: Visit 1 procedures may be conducted over more than 1 day if all activities are completed within the allowable visit tolerance.
studyChanges.summary: Modified Visit 1 procedure timing requirement to reference allowable visit tolerance
